# Example CODEOWNERS entries for a paik/ folder - see ../ROLES.md for the reasoning behind
# this split. Copy the lines you want into your repo's real CODEOWNERS file and adjust the
# team handles; this file on its own does nothing (GitHub/GitLab only read a CODEOWNERS file
# at the repo root or in .github/ or docs/).

# Product-owned: project-level scope, roadmap, and delivery links
/paik/project.md              @your-org/product

# Engineering-owned: component definitions
/paik/component.md            @your-org/platform-eng
/paik/components/             @your-org/platform-eng

# Operator/SRE-owned: environments and their operational links
/paik/environments/           @your-org/sre
